### 5.6 FABRICATION SEQUENCE

**Step 1: Inner Wall Fabrication (Weeks 1-20)**
1. Source fused silica blanks (2 weeks)
2. Precision grinding to toroidal shape (12 weeks)
3. Optical polishing (3 weeks)
4. Quality inspection (ultrasonic + optical) (1 week)
5. Thermal cycling test (2 weeks)

**Step 2: Outer Shell Fabrication (Weeks 8-20)**
1. Roll stainless steel sheets (1 week)
2. TIG weld toroidal sections (4 weeks)
3. Heat treatment (solution anneal) (1 week)
4. Machine port openings (2 weeks)
5. Electropolish interior (2 weeks)
6. Leak test (helium mass spec) (1 week)
7. Weld CF flanges (1 week)

**Step 3: Assembly (Weeks 20-24)**
1. Position inner silica torus (precision alignment)
2. Insert thermal standoffs (ceramic, low conductivity)
3. Seal inner-outer gap with indium wire gaskets
4. Vacuum test entire assembly
5. Bake out at 200Â°C for 72 hours
6. Final leak check (<10â»Â¹â° TorrÂ·L/s)

**Critical Tolerances:**
- Toroidal symmetry: <0.5 mm deviation
- Surface flatness: <Î»/10 (for 633nm)
- Port alignment: <0.2Â° angular error

