### 6.7 SHELL ASSEMBLY PROCEDURE

**Integration Sequence (From Inside Out):**

1. **Install Shell 1:**
   - Position on bearing supports (temporary scaffolding)
   - Align with plasma chamber center
   - Mount 12 bearings to shell 1
   - Attach 6 motors (stators on shell 2 mounts, waiting)
   - Connect encoders and wiring
   - Test rotation: Spin up to 27 Hz, verify balance

2. **Install Shell 2:**
   - Lower shell 2 over shell 1
   - Mount shell 2 bearings to shell 1 support frame
   - Complete motor connections (shell 1 rotors to shell 2 stators)
   - Install shell 2 motors (stators on shell 3 mounts)
   - Test: Spin shell 1 (27 Hz) and shell 2 (81 Hz), verify no interference

3. **Repeat for Shells 3-5**
   - Same procedure, increasing care with balance

4. **Install Shells 6-7 (Maglev):**
   - Install superconducting coil arrays
   - Cool to 4.2 K (liquid helium)
   - Levitate shell and verify clearances
   - Engage rotating stator field
   - Ramp up to operating speed (6,561 Hz, then 19,683 Hz)

**Total Assembly Time:** 8-12 weeks (with 3-person crew)

### 6.8 STRUCTURAL ANALYSIS

**Centrifugal Stress (Shell 7, Worst Case):**

```
Shell 7:
- Radius: R = 4.558 m
- Angular velocity: Ï‰ = 2Ï€ Ã— 19,683 Hz = 123,660 rad/s
- Tangential velocity: v = Ï‰R = 563,600 m/s (!!)
  
  âš ï¸ THIS IS 0.188% SPEED OF LIGHT! âš ï¸
  
Centrifugal acceleration: a = Ï‰Â²R = 6.97 Ã— 10Â¹â° m/sÂ²
                             = 7.1 Ã— 10â¹ g's

Stress in shell wall: Ïƒ = Ï Ï‰Â² RÂ²
                        = 1580 kg/mÂ³ Ã— (123,660 rad/s)Â² Ã— (4.558 m)Â²
                        = 4.0 Ã— 10Â¹Â¹ Pa = 400 GPa
                        
Material strength (CFRP): 7 GPa

FAILURE RATIO: 400 / 7 = 57Ã— OVER STRENGTH LIMIT!

âŒ MECHANICAL ROTATION AT 19,683 Hz IS IMPOSSIBLE âŒ
```

**REVISED APPROACH - ELECTROMAGNETIC "ROTATION":**

Instead of physical rotation, shell 7 uses:
- **Rotating magnetic field** (no mass movement)
- **Induced currents** in superconducting shell
- **Effective "rotation"** of EM fields (not matter)

This decouples physical structure from impossible centrifugal loads!

**New Design for Shells 6 & 7:**
- **Shell composition:** Superconducting film (YBCO or MgBâ‚‚)
- **Substrate:** Non-rotating structural shell
- **Rotation:** EM fields only (via external stator coils)
- **Achievable:** YES - no material stress!

