## SECTION 12: SENSOR & DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEMS

### 12.1 PLASMA DIAGNOSTICS

**Thomson Scattering (Electron Temperature & Density):**
- **Laser:** Nd:YAG, 532 nm, 1 J/pulse, 10 Hz
- **Detection:** Gated ICCD camera + spectrometer
- **Range:** T_e = 10 eV to 10 keV, n_e = 10^18 to 10^21 mâ»Â³
- **Cost:** $285,000

**Langmuir Probes (Floating Potential):**
- **Count:** 6 (insertable via ports)
- **Bias voltage:** Â±100 V, swept
- **Current measurement:** pA to mA
- **Cost:** $12,000 total

**Spectroscopy (Line Emission):**
- **Spectrometer:** Ocean Optics HR4000 (UV-VIS-NIR)
- **Fiber optics:** 6Ã— viewing chords
- **Analysis:** Identifies impurities, measures T_ion
- **Cost:** $35,000

**Interferometry (Line-Integrated Density):**
- **Type:** Michelson interferometer, 10.6 Î¼m (COâ‚‚ laser)
- **Chords:** 3Ã— (vertical, horizontal, diagonal)
- **Resolution:** 10^17 mâ»Â²
- **Cost:** $95,000

**Bolometry (Radiated Power):**
- **Sensors:** AXUV photodiodes (absolute calibration)
- **Count:** 24 (toroidal + poloidal coverage)
- **Range:** Soft X-ray to visible
- **Cost:** $18,000

**Total Plasma Diagnostics:** ~$445,000

### 12.2 TOPOLOGICAL DIAGNOSTICS

**Quantum Entanglement Witness:**
- **Method:** Bell inequality test on photon pairs
- **Detectors:** Single-photon avalanche diodes (SPADs)
- **Count:** 4 (Bell test requires 2 pairs)
- **Coincidence electronics:** PicoQuant HydraHarp 400
- **Cost:** $145,000

**Wormhole Throat Imaging:**
- **Concept:** Gravitational lensing of background light
- **Camera:** High-speed (10,000 fps), CMOS
- **Lens:** Wide-angle (180Â° FOV)
- **Illumination:** Laser grid (structured light)
- **Cost:** $85,000

**Spacetime Curvature Sensor:**
- **Type:** Atom interferometer (ultra-sensitive accelerometer)
- **Sensitivity:** 10â»Â¹â° g (detects metric perturbations)
- **Manufacturer:** AOSense or Muquans
- **Cost:** $450,000 (!)

**Total Topological Diagnostics:** ~$680,000

### 12.3 DATA ACQUISITION SYSTEM

**Requirements:**
- **Channels:** ~500 analog inputs
- **Sample rate:** 1 MHz (fast transients)
- **Resolution:** 16-bit
- **Storage:** 10 TB (per experiment)

**Hardware:**
- **DAQ chassis:** National Instruments PXIe-1095
- **Digitizer cards:** PXIe-6366 (8 channels each, Ã— 65)
- **FPGA processing:** PXIe-7976R (real-time analysis)
- **Storage:** NAS (Synology RS4021xs+)

**Cost:** ~$385,000

