## SECTION 15: EMERGENCY SHUTDOWN SYSTEMS

### 15.1 FAST PLASMA SHUTDOWN

**Trigger Conditions:**
- Loss of vacuum (P > 10â»â´ Torr)
- Loss of cooling (Î”T > 5Â°C/min)
- Magnetic field quench
- Manual E-stop

**Shutdown Sequence (Automatic):**
1. **T+0 ms:** Interrupt RF power (all generators)
2. **T+10 ms:** Open gas injection valves (Ar flood)
3. **T+50 ms:** Activate magnetic quench (dump resistors)
4. **T+100 ms:** Vent chamber to atmosphere (relief valves)

**Result:** Plasma extinguished in <200 ms, no damage

### 15.2 MAGNETIC QUENCH PROTECTION

**Quench Detection:**
- **Method:** Voltage monitoring across each coil
- **Threshold:** >0.1 V (indicates resistive transition)
- **Response:** <5 ms

**Energy Dump:**
- **Dump resistors:** 12Ã— 0.05 Î©, 1 MW each
- **Stored energy:** 75 MJ per coil â†’ Dissipated as heat
- **Dump time:** 10 seconds (controlled ramp-down)

**Cost:** $85,000 (quench protection system)

### 15.3 FIRE SUPPRESSION

**System Type:** Clean agent (FM-200 or Novec 1230)
- **Coverage:** Entire room (400 mÂ²)
- **Discharge time:** <10 seconds
- **Detection:** Smoke + heat (dual-zone)

**Cost:** $55,000

