- ANSI Z136.1 (Laser safety)
- NFPA 70E (Electrical safety)
- OSHA 1910 (General industry)

## APPENDIX C: SIMULATION & MODELING

**Recommended Software:**
- **Plasma:** COMSOL Multiphysics (plasma module)
- **Magnetics:** Opera (Vector Fields)
- **Vacuum:** MolFlow+ (Monte Carlo)
- **Structural:** ANSYS Mechanical
- **Thermal:** Thermal Desktop (C&R)
- **RF:** CST Microwave Studio

## APPENDIX D: SAFETY CONSIDERATIONS

**Hazards:**
1. **High voltage:** Up to 50 kV (RF, magnets)
2. **High current:** Up to 12,000 A (magnets)
3. **Cryogens:** Liquid helium (asphyxiation, cold burns)
4. **Vacuum:** Implosion risk (atmospheric pressure)
5. **Radiation:** X-rays from plasma (shielding required)
6. **Magnetic fields:** 8 Tesla (pacemaker hazard, projectiles)
7. **Rotating machinery:** Shells up to 1,180,980 RPM (energy storage)

**Required PPE:**
- Arc flash suits (when working on energized equipment)
- Cryogenic gloves (LHe handling)
- Safety glasses (always in facility)
- Hearing protection (vacuum pumps, motors)

**Safety Systems:**
- Interlocked access doors
- Emergency stop buttons (6 locations)
- Oxygen monitors (cryogen areas)
- Radiation badges (personnel monitoring)
- Fire suppression (FM-200)

